<font color="#FF0000">I'LL REMEMBER JOLLY 365</font><br>
<tt>Sat Oct 18  2:26:43 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Veterans Day this year will focus my attention, whether I make it to Arlington on November 19th or not, on the crew of Jolly 365 and their families.  For them the Vietnam War is finally drawing to a close.  Those guy's kids are now in their twenties or older, and have formed associations so that they can share their experiences.  Some are setting up web sites dedicated to the memories of their fathers who were lost.  They are still feeling the sorrow of loss, but also the pride of the mission their fathers were conducting that day.  My thoughts, feelings and prayers will be with them this Veteran's Day.  The crew has returned after over 25 years away; happy or sad, that's the news for me.  
